18ca93a6 [claude-opus-4-6] #• One thought on hex* — since you're targeting assembly use, consider whether you want the
18ca93a6 [claude-opus-4-6] #hex field zero-padded to 4 characters consistently (which you're already doing) and whether a `$`
18ca93a6 [claude-opus-4-6] #prefix would be useful or just noise. Probably leave it bare since the consumer can format it
18ca93a6 [claude-opus-4-6] #however they need.
