18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #Here's how the ball movement works in Woz's Breakout:
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #• Ball Position Variables:*
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- `X` = horizontal position (0-39)
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- `Y` = vertical position (0-119, but divided by 3 for display)
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- `V` = horizontal velocity (-1 left, 1 right)
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- `W` = vertical velocity (-2 to +2)
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #• Movement Loop (Lines 50-90):*
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #1. Calculate new position: `J = Y + W` (vertical), `I = X + V` (horizontal)
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #2. Wall collisions: If `J` goes out of bounds (0-119), reverse `W`
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #3. Paddle collision: If `I = 0` (left wall/paddle), calculate new trajectory based on where
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #ball hits paddle
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #4. Brick collisions: Check `SCRN(I, K)` at new position; if not background color, brick hit
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #5. Update display: Erase old ball, draw new ball
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #• Key Physics:*
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- Vertical bounce: Simple `W = -W` reversal
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- Paddle bounce: Angle depends on where ball hits paddle: `W = (K-P)*2-5`
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- Brick hits: Ball continues horizontally (`V = ABS(V)`), brick disappears
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- Sound effects: `PEEK(-16336)` accesses speaker click
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #• Initialization (Line 40):*
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- Random starting angle: `W = RND(5)-2` (-2 to +2)
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #- Always starts moving left: `V = -1`
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #The ball moves in straight lines with simple integer arithmetic, bouncing only on
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #vertical/horizontal surfaces.
18dde713 [deepseek-chat] #
