18dfaaa8 [nitro@ryzen5] how to read vic20 joy port
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #The VIC-20 joystick port is read via VIA#1 (6522) at addresses 9111 (Port A) and
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #9120 (Port B).
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #Pin Mapping
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #╭─────────────┬────────────────┬─────────┬───────────╮
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Direction  │  VIA Register  │  Bit    │  Address  │
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #├─────────────┼────────────────┼─────────┼───────────┤
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Up         │  Port A        │  bit 2  │  $9111    │
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Down       │  Port A        │  bit 3  │  $9111    │
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Left       │  Port A        │  bit 4  │  $9111    │
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Fire       │  Port A        │  bit 5  │  $9111    │
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Right      │  Port B        │  bit 7  │  $9120    │
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #╰─────────────┴────────────────┴─────────┴───────────╯
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #All bits are active low (0 = pressed, 1 = released).
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #6502 Assembly
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #readjoy:
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #    lda $9111       ; VIA#1 Port A
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #    and #%00111100  ; mask bits 2-5 (up, down, left, fire)
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #    sta joyval
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #    lda $9120       ; VIA#1 Port B
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #    and #%10000000  ; mask bit 7 (right)
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #    ora joyval
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #    eor #%10111100  ; invert so 1 = pressed
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #    sta joyval
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #    rts
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #joyval: .byte 0
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #After the call, `joyval` bits mean (1 = active):
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Bit 2: Up
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Bit 3: Down
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Bit 4: Left
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Bit 5: Fire
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Bit 7: Right
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #BASIC equivalent
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #10 A = PEEK(37137) : B = PEEK(37152)
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #20 UP = (A AND 4) = 0
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #30 DN = (A AND 8) = 0
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #40 LF = (A AND 16) = 0
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #50 FR = (A AND 32) = 0
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #60 RT = (B AND 128) = 0
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #The split across two VIA ports is a common gotcha — right is the odd one out on Port B.
18dfab61 [claude-opus-4-6] #
