18dfadb6 [nitro@ryzen5] how to read paddle buttons
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #The VIC-20 paddle buttons are read from the same VIA#1 ports as the joystick, sharing some
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #lines.
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #Paddle Button Mapping
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #╭───────────────┬────────────────┬───────┬──────────╮
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Button       │  VIA Register  │  Bit  │  Address │
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #├───────────────┼────────────────┼───────┼──────────┤
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Paddle 1 btn │  Port A        │  bit 2│  $9111   │
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Paddle 2 btn │  Port A        │  bit 4│  $9111   │
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #╰───────────────┴────────────────┴───────┴──────────╯
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #Active low (0 = pressed).
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #These are the same lines as joystick Up and Left — the VIC-20 doesn't distinguish; it's the
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #same electrical connection.
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #Paddle Analog Values (Resistance)
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #The paddle positions are read via the SID-less analog inputs routed to VIA#1 Timer.
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #The VIC-20 uses the POT lines on the control port, read through:
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #╭───────────────┬──────────╮
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Paddle 1 (X) │  $9008   │  (POT X)
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #│  Paddle 2 (Y) │  $9009   │  (POT Y)
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #╰───────────────┴──────────╯
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #Wait — those aren't quite right. The VIC-20 doesn't have SID POT registers. The paddles are
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #actually read via:
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #$9008  -  Paddle X (analog value, 0-255)
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #$9009  -  Paddle Y (analog value, 0-255)
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #These are VIC chip registers, not VIA.
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #6502 Assembly
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #readpaddle:
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	lda $9008       ; paddle 1 position (0-255)
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	sta padx
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	lda $9009       ; paddle 2 position (0-255)
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	sta pady
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	lda $9111       ; VIA#1 Port A
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	and #%00000100  ; bit 2
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	eor #%00000100  ; invert: 1 = pressed
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	sta btn1
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	lda $9111
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	and #%00010000  ; bit 4
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	eor #%00010000
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	sta btn2
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #	rts
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #padx:	.byte 0
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #pady:	.byte 0
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #btn1:	.byte 0
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #btn2:	.byte 0
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #BASIC
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #10 PX = PEEK(36872) : REM PADDLE 1 POSITION
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #20 PY = PEEK(36873) : REM PADDLE 2 POSITION
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #30 B1 = (PEEK(37137) AND 4) = 0 : REM PADDLE 1 BUTTON
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #40 B2 = (PEEK(37137) AND 16) = 0 : REM PADDLE 2 BUTTON
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #Notes
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #- Paddle analog values can be noisy — averaging a few reads helps.
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #- The analog values update continuously via the VIC chip's internal sampling.
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #- Since buttons share joystick lines, you can't reliably use both simultaneously.
18dfaebe [claude-opus-4-6] #
