18e3028b [nitro@ryzen5] docs for ql basic circle command
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #QBasic CIRCLE Command
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #CIRCLE (x, y), radius [, color [, start, end [, aspect]]]
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #• Parameters:*
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- (x, y) – Center coordinates of the circle/ellipse
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- radius – Radius in pixels
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- color – Color attribute (optional)
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- start, end – Arc angles in radians (optional, range: -2π to 2π). Negative values draw a
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #line from the center to that arc endpoint (pie slices).
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- aspect – Aspect ratio (optional). Values other than 1.0 draw ellipses. Default depends on
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #screen mode.
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #• Examples:*
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #SCREEN 12
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #' Basic circle
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #CIRCLE (320, 240), 100
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #' Circle with color
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #CIRCLE (320, 240), 100, 4
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #' Arc (quarter circle)
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #CIRCLE (320, 240), 100, 4, 0, 1.5708
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #' Pie slice (negative angles draw radii to center)
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #CIRCLE (320, 240), 100, 4, -0.5, -2.5
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #' Ellipse (aspect ratio 0.5 = wide)
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #CIRCLE (320, 240), 100, 4, , , 0.5
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #• Notes:*
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Angles are in radians, not degrees. (π = 3.14159...)
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- 0 radians = 3 o'clock, π/2 = 12 o'clock, π = 9 o'clock, 3π/2 = 6 o'clock.
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- To convert degrees to radians: `radians = degrees * 3.14159 / 180`
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Omitted optional parameters still need their commas as placeholders (as shown in the ellipse
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #example).
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #- The `PAINT` command can be used afterward to fill the shape.
18e30331 [claude-opus-4-6] #
