18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #Nice work, this is well structured. Here are the issues I found:
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #Opcode Errors
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #- TSX — flags should be `"NZ"`, not `""`. It affects N and Z based on the value
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #transferred.
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #Opcode Verification
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #All hex opcodes check out correctly against the NMOS 6502 reference. Good job there.
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #BRK Note
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #- BRK — you list flags as `""`. It does set the B and I flags on the stack/in status.
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #Whether you want to reflect that is a design choice, but worth noting. You could argue `"I"` at
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #minimum since it sets the interrupt disable flag.
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #STA Missing Opcode
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #- STA has 7 opcodes listed but the standard 8 addressing modes for store-to-memory include
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #all except immediate. You're missing STA absolute,Y ... wait, no — `99` is there. Let me
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #recount: `85 95 8D 9D 99 81 91` — that's 7, which is correct. STA has no immediate mode. ✓
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #Profile Section
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #This is harder to fully validate without knowing your spec index mapping, but I notice:
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Spec 5 (branches): `{"bytes":[2],"cycles":[2]}` — branch cycles are 2 (not taken), 3
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #(taken, same page), 4 (taken, page cross). You only list one cycle count. Might be intentional
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #simplification?
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Spec 8 (JMP): `{"bytes":[3,3],"cycles":[3,5]}` — JMP absolute is 3 cycles, JMP indirect
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #is 5. ✓
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Spec 15 (LDA etc.): `(indirect,X)` is 6 cycles, `(indirect),Y` is 5 (+1 page cross). You
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #have `6,5` at the end. ✓
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Spec 13 (LDX/LDY): 5 modes listed but LDX uses zeropage,Y not zeropage,X and LDY uses
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #zeropage,X not zeropage,Y — the addressing modes differ between LDX and LDY so sharing a single
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #spec index may be misleading if the mode list is implied from the global `addressmode` array.
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #Minor
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #- Copyright says 2026 — time traveller? 😄
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #Overall it's solid and clearly carefully assembled.
18f8f9e9 [claude-opus-4-6] #
