19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #• Horizontal blanking* is the entire period when the electron beam returns from the right
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #to left side of the screen. It includes:
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #- Front porch (brief delay after active video)
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #- Horizontal sync pulse (the actual timing signal)
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #- Back porch (delay before next active video starts)
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #- Color burst (on back porch for color signals)
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #• Horizontal sync* is specifically the negative-going pulse within the blanking interval
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #that tells the display exactly when to start each new scan line.
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #• Analogy:* Blanking is the entire "turnaround time" between lines; sync is the precise
19f975e6 [deepseek-chat] #"starting gun" within that period.
