1a8720d3 [claude-opus-4-6] #Yes, S/PDIF over TOSLINK (optical) is license-free. It's an old Sony/Philips standard that's been
1a8720d3 [claude-opus-4-6] #open for decades.
1a8720d3 [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8720d4 [claude-opus-4-6] #It's also a great fit for PIO - it's a single-pin biphase mark encoded serial stream at relatively
1a8720d4 [claude-opus-4-6] #low bitrates (3.072 MHz for 48kHz stereo 16-bit). There are existing PIO implementations for RP2040
1a8720d4 [claude-opus-4-6] #that work directly on RP2350.
1a8720d4 [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8720d5 [claude-opus-4-6] #So DVI video over HDMI connector + TOSLINK audio would give you a fully license-free setup with
1a8720d5 [claude-opus-4-6] #digital AV output.
1a8720d5 [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8720d6 [claude-opus-4-6] #A TOSLINK transmitter module is just an LED driver - a few dollars for something like a DLT1111 or
1a8720d6 [claude-opus-4-6] #similar, driven directly from a GPIO/PIO pin.
1a8720d6 [claude-opus-4-6] #
