1a8b4770 [claude-opus-4-6] #The limit is on BCK - the PCM5102 specs max 50.4MHz for the bit clock.
1a8b4770 [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4770 [claude-opus-4-6] #Your BCK is 3MHz, well within spec. The sample rate is just a consequence:
1a8b4770 [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4771 [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4771 [claude-opus-4-6] #BCK / bits per sample frame = sample rate
1a8b4771 [claude-opus-4-6] #3MHz / 64 = 46,875 Hz
1a8b4771 [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4772 [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4772 [claude-opus-4-6] #The 64 comes from 16 bits × 2 channels × 2 PIO cycles per bit (your 4-instruction loop). If you
1a8b4772 [claude-opus-4-6] #wanted higher sample rate you could either increase BCK or reduce bit depth - but 46,875 Hz is
1a8b4772 [claude-opus-4-6] #plenty for a synth.
1a8b4773 [claude-opus-4-6] #
