1a8b4e8b [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4e8b [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4e8b [claude-opus-4-6] #150MHz / (N cycles per bit × 32 bits) = sample rate
1a8b4e8b [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4e8b [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4e8d [claude-opus-4-6] #For 48,000 Hz: 150MHz / 48000 / 32 = 97.65 cycles per bit - not integer.
1a8b4e8d [claude-opus-4-6] #
1a8b4e8d [claude-opus-4-6] #For 46,875 Hz: 150MHz / 46875 / 32 = 100 cycles per bit. That's your current setup (divider 25 × 4
